      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SHES CRUNCHY NZ (5) has the hoof on the till after seconds in her two starts at this circuit and distance since crossing from NZ. Registered a strong performance last time when she battled on bravely to be beaten less than 2m. Draws a little wider but should be peaking third-up. EUREKA JO (2) has placed in two of three starts since joining Chantal Turpin. Came from wider to be beaten 2.7m last week so is better served by this barrier and has yet to miss the top-three in four tries at this distance, winning twice. DRAW A DREAM (9) will be fitter for two Sydney starts off a long spell including a fresh placing. Draws on the back row but won her lone try at the distance and she was a Group 1 winning youngster so has class when right. MARDIBRINGSAPARTY (8) showed good improvement for a 2.5m third last week. Building a handy record at this circuit and distance and can progress further third-up.",
